# GPU-enabled PyTorch installation (CUDA 12.8)
# This file defines the top-level PyTorch dependencies for GPU systems
# Use: uv pip install -r requirements-gpu.in
# Or compile: uv pip compile requirements-gpu.in -o requirements-gpu.txt --python-version 3.11
# Note: NVIDIA CUDA dependencies are platform-specific and managed by PyTorch

# For Docker/production, use in Dockerfile:
#   pip install torch torchvision --index-url https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cu128

# CUDA 12.8 is compatible with:
# - Driver 570.00 or newer
# - RTX 40/50 series (Ada Lovelace/Blackwell), RTX 30 series (Ampere), and newer
# - Provides better performance and supports latest GPU architectures

--index-url https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cu128
torch
torchvision
